An intelligence-driven operation was conducted in the Phalaborwa, Limpopo, area after information was received that there were people selling lion heads, according to police spokesperson Brigadier Motlafela Mojapelo, Letaba Herald reports. According to Mojapelo, a police trap was set up, and five suspects aged between 38 and 70 were arrested. The suspects were found in possession of a lion s head. READ MORE: Manhunt launched after lions were mutilated outside Tzaneen &#8220;The provincial commissioner, Lieutenant-General Nneke Ledwaba, commended the swiftness in which the members utilised the information. He then went further to thank members of the community for their involvement in providing the information,&#8221; Mojapelo said. The possibility of linking this to similar incidents in the province are under way. WARNING GRAPHIC IMAGE: Picture: SAPS Caxton News Service For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.